                        <h1> Color Sensor</h1>
                        <ul>
                            <li><p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i>These sensors are photoelectric devices that can emit light and detect the color of reflected light from an object.</p></li>
                            <br>
                            <li><p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i>These sensors can detect the intensity of light reflected from an object and differentiates the primary colors like red, blue, and green. These are also called color detectors.</p></li>
                            <br>
                            <li><p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i>This sensor usually detects color on the RBG scale. This sensor can categorize the color as red, blue, or green..</p></li>
                            <br>
                            <li><p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i>These sensors are also equipped with filters to reject the unwanted IR light and UV light.</p></li>
                            <br>
                            <li><p><i class="fa fa-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i>This sensor detects the color of material three main types of equipment is required. A light source to illuminate the material surface, a surface whose color has to be detected, and the receivers which can measure the reflected wavelengths.</p></li>
                        </ul>
